    {
      "para_id": "p2",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 2,
      "text": "U.di.Con. APS – Union for the Defence of Consumers, included in the list of consumer associations and representative users at national level referred to in Article 137 of Legislative Decree No 206 of 6 September 2005 and member of the National Council of Consumers and Users (CNCU), with reference to the text set out above, summarises the following comments.",
      "char_len": 359,
      "chunk_word_count": 60,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9302325581395349,
        "digit": 0.036544850498338874,
        "non_space": 0.8384401114206128
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9476744186046513,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p3",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 3,
      "text": "The aim of this association is to protect and protect consumers, who, from the perspective under consideration, can be defined as the direct addressees of the initiative in question.",
      "char_len": 182,
      "chunk_word_count": 29,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.974025974025974,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8461538461538461
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6902417027417027,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p4",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 4,
      "text": "It is well known that in today's world, consumers play a crucial role in the social economy of markets in general: they are the demand for goods and services offered by businesses, and this is clearly also true in the digital market.",
      "char_len": 233,
      "chunk_word_count": 42,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9739583333333334,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8240343347639485
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8888020833333334,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p5",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 5,
      "text": "**Strengthening the transparency of this sector is therefore crucial.**",
      "char_len": 71,
      "chunk_word_count": 9,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9206349206349206,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8873239436619719
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.3904761904761905,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p6",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 6,
      "text": "It should be noted that this EU effort is in a context of continuity and harmony with previous initiatives already studied by the European Commission (the Digital Services Act and the Digital Markets Act).",
      "char_len": 205,
      "chunk_word_count": 34,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9825581395348837,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8390243902439024
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7730297157622739,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "Moreover, it is clear that digital markets have a profound influence on consumers' habits throughout the decision-making process, from the initial choice stage to the final stage, linked to the purchase and enjoyment of the good (or service).",
      "char_len": 242,
      "chunk_word_count": 38,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9609756097560975,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8471074380165289
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8179539295392955,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "For this reason – given that the consumer's point of view must necessarily be taken into account – we welcome the start of this work.",
      "char_len": 133,
      "chunk_word_count": 23,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.963302752293578,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8195488721804511
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.590532619775739,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "Via di Santa Croce in Jerusalem, 63-00185 Rome RM – Tel. 06.77250783 – info@udicon.org – www.udicon.org",
      "char_len": 103,
      "chunk_word_count": 18,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.6818181818181818,
        "digit": 0.19318181818181818,
        "non_space": 0.8543689320388349
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.303030303030303,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission"
      ],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "it therefore sets out a series of reflections and a number of essential requirements for consumers in the use of these digital services.",
      "char_len": 136,
      "chunk_word_count": 23,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9912280701754386,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8382352941176471
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6114766081871346,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "General principles"
      ],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "Fully endorses the idea behind this initiative, which is also aimed at protecting consumers' position in the digital world at European level; indeed, it is now known that the digital transformation has profoundly changed the way consumers interact with markets.",
      "char_len": 261,
      "chunk_word_count": 40,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9774774774774775,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8505747126436781
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8608858858858859,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "General principles"
      ],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "These new interactions expose consumers (first market stakeholders) to new forms of vulnerability, such as those currently being studied, such as dark patterns and the use of deceptive images in digital interfaces.",
      "char_len": 214,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9726775956284153,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8551401869158879
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.735063752276867,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p13",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Need for action at EU level."
      ],
      "ordinal": 13,
      "text": "Given the spread of these unfair practices in digital markets (as above), it becomes clear that fragmented action, limited to individual Member States, would be insufficient and ineffective to overcome these problems.",
      "char_len": 217,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.967741935483871,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8571428571428571
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7313620071684588,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p14",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Need for action at EU level."
      ],
      "ordinal": 14,
      "text": "The very characteristics of digital markets require a coordinated and harmonised response at European level: individual states cannot effectively regulate a supranational phenomenon by its very nature, such as online.",
      "char_len": 217,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9840425531914894,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8663594470046083
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7130319148936171,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p15",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Need for action at EU level."
      ],
      "ordinal": 15,
      "text": "In this context, the introduction of a harmonised legal framework that explicitly prohibits dark patterns and strictly regulates the use of visual content in digital interfaces is of paramount importance.",
      "char_len": 204,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9885714285714285,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8578431372549019
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7164285714285714,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p16",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Need for action at EU level."
      ],
      "ordinal": 16,
      "text": "For the same reasons, a European approach is needed to effectively tackle other issues in consultation as well, such as: digital dependence and its economic impact, protection of minors on the network, regulation of influencers and transparency of tariffs and contracts.",
      "char_len": 270,
      "chunk_word_count": 41,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9739130434782609,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8518518518518519
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8734903381642513,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p17",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 17,
      "text": "It seems appropriate to start with considerations on dark patterns.",
      "char_len": 67,
      "chunk_word_count": 10,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9827586206896551,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8656716417910447
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.4370689655172414,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p18",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 18,
      "text": "Via di Santa Croce in Jerusalem, 63-00185 Rome RM – Tel. 06.77250783 - info@udicon.org - www.udicon.org",
      "char_len": 103,
      "chunk_word_count": 18,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.6818181818181818,
        "digit": 0.19318181818181818,
        "non_space": 0.8543689320388349
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.303030303030303,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p19",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 19,
      "text": "These practices are undoubtedly particularly odious, as they are misleading for consumers: dark patterns arise precisely in order to make consumers choose goods or services they would not have chosen otherwise.",
      "char_len": 210,
      "chunk_word_count": 31,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9833333333333333,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8571428571428571
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7277777777777777,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "Notwithstanding this element of certainty, the category is complex to delimit, since it consists of numerous computer techniques and variants.",
      "char_len": 142,
      "chunk_word_count": 20,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.975609756097561,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8661971830985915
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5539295392953929,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "As a result, in order to avoid fragmented action in the European context, it is necessary to start from the bottom up, through regulatory intervention aimed at defining first and foremost the concept of digital dark patterns, with particular reference to the scope of unfair commercial practices. In this sense, it would seem appropriate to draw up objective and subjective indicators that make it possible to identify dark patterns in order to assess their suitability in digital contexts (websites, apps, etc.).",
      "char_len": 513,
      "chunk_word_count": 81,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9722863741339491,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8440545808966862
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9792147806004619,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "In this activity, it is important to listen to the consumer's feedback, who may be affected by the phenomenon in question. It is therefore appropriate to create tools for collecting and analysing consumer feedback on the platforms themselves, which can also distinguish sites into various categories of transparency (e.g. the provision of different colour stickers, where the colour 'green' means that the page is safe and reliable, conversely 'yellow', unsafe and unreliable 'red').",
      "char_len": 483,
      "chunk_word_count": 74,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9537712895377128,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8509316770186336
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9653284671532847,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "In parallel, it is desirable to adopt common design standards that are transparent, accessible and non-manipulative, to be integrated as general European guidelines for consumer protection in the digital world.",
      "char_len": 210,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9723756906077348,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.861904761904762
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7042817679558011,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "At this point, it is appropriate to briefly reflect on the harmful nature of this extensive practice and the problems identified in the consultation.",
      "char_len": 149,
      "chunk_word_count": 24,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9841269841269841,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8456375838926175
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6214285714285714,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "The topic can certainly not be underestimated: it is recalled that in the text underlying the consultation, this economic impact is estimated (downwards) at EUR 7.9 billion per year. In our view, it should be recalled that behind this number there is a multiplicity of practices affecting web users, especially the most vulnerable.",
      "char_len": 331,
      "chunk_word_count": 54,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9605734767025089,
        "digit": 0.007168458781362007,
        "non_space": 0.8429003021148036
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9704301075268817,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p26",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 26,
      "text": "Among the most alarming practices is the excessive use of buy now pay laterservices, which can easily induce consumers (even very young people) to borrow beyond their possibilities.",
      "char_len": 181,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.974025974025974,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.850828729281768
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.674963924963925,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p27",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 27,
      "text": "Via di Santa Croce in Jerusalem, 63-00185 Rome RM – Tel. 06.77250783 - info@udicon.org - www.udicon.org",
      "char_len": 103,
