      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 28,
      "text": "Similarly, from a financial point of view, some video games are structured in such a way as to be ‘pay to win’ or ‘pay to progress’. These are video games which, although formally open to all, make it extremely difficult for non-paying players to be competitive. This induces gamers (even very young people) to buy continuously in order to be competitive, with investments that can also be substantial (on this point, the following is emblematic: https://www.money.it/spende-eur33780-app-figlio-padre-perde-causa-contro-go-).",
      "char_len": 525,
      "chunk_word_count": 84,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9133333333333333,
        "digit": 0.011111111111111112,
        "non_space": 0.8571428571428571
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.935,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p29",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 29,
      "text": "Digital dependencies are linked to this issue. EU regulation should avoid any addiction, both in relation to video games (so-called binge gaming) and in relation to platforms (social media and beyond).",
      "char_len": 201,
      "chunk_word_count": 31,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9532163742690059,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8507462686567164
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7051900584795322,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p30",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 30,
      "text": "Similarly, it is not those who do not see the need to regulate the activity of influencers more closely, in two respects in particular: advertising and ‘scientific’ councils.",
      "char_len": 174,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9591836734693877,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8448275862068966
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6638321995464853,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p31",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 31,
      "text": "It is not acceptable to circulate content on platforms where influencers carry out, in an incorrect manner, promotional activities for any product or service, or activities that should be reserved to qualified persons (e.g. nutrition, where young people might be vulnerable).",
      "char_len": 275,
      "chunk_word_count": 42,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9617021276595744,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8545454545454545
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8796099290780142,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p32",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 32,
      "text": "A further issue, which requires stricter regulation, as set out in the consultation document, is transparency in terms of tariffs and contract management. Digital makes contact between businesses and consumers much easier, but this simplification must not lead to superficiality. This therefore requires European rules on minimum transparency elements in online contracts and in the display of tariffs.",
      "char_len": 402,
      "chunk_word_count": 58,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9797101449275363,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8582089552238806
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9847826086956523,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p33",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 33,
      "text": "In conclusion, all these issues undoubtedly make it desirable for the EU to intervene, and U.Di.Con. is at your disposal to explore the individual issues if deemed appropriate.",
      "char_len": 176,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.959731543624161,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8465909090909091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6947986577181208,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p34",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "The European Commission",
        "Substance"
      ],
      "ordinal": 34,
      "text": "Regulatory harmonisation at European level.",
      "char_len": 43,
      "chunk_word_count": 5,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9743589743589743,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.9069767441860465
